Ian S.~

Thanks for everyoneâ€™s feedback on my QtChart prototype program. Iâ€™ve cleaned up my resource collection of images and stored them in the main program but not in the exported example programs. I also found a way to make the splitter handles have an image and some colour. The python/css-ish code isâ€¦

    self.splitter.setStyleSheet(""",
    QSplitter::handle {
    background-color: skyblue;
    image: url(:/images/horizontal_splitter.svg);
    height: 12px;

    }
    QSplitter::handle:pressed {
    background-color: rgb(100, 200, 255);
    image: url(:/images/horizontal_splitter_pressed.svg);
    }""")

...I'll show you at next months meeting.

Peter R.~

