2022-05-09

WebSockets Server

Details

There are different ways of adding dynamism to pages coming from your Web server. You may have heard of â€œAJAXâ€ (â€œasynchronous JavaScript and XmlHttpRequestâ€). The next level beyond that is called â€œWebSocketsâ€, which creates a server connection that allows for an ongoing stream of messages in both directions, to implement a live, continuously-updating Web page.
Lawrence will demonstrate how to write a simple WebSockets server in Python, using one of the existing server frameworks that implement ASGI, the Asynchronous Server Gateway Interface.

